Razorpay vs CCAvenue — Why Razorpay may be preferred


| Feature                              | CCAvenue                 | Razorpay                            | Why Razorpay could be chosen                     |
| ------------------------------------ | ------------------------ | ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| **Ease of integration**              | Moderate, older API      | Modern API, Rails/JS SDKs           | Faster dev integration; less boilerplate         |
| **Webhooks & callbacks**             | Available but older docs | Well-documented, developer-friendly | Easier for real-time payment updates in Rails    |
| **UPI & wallets support**            | Yes, but slower updates  | Yes, robust                         | Better for mobile-first apps                     |
| **Subscriptions/Recurring payments** | Limited support          | Strong built-in support             | Needed if app had recurring orders or SaaS model |
| **Developer experience**             | Steeper learning curve   | Simple, modern dashboards           | Saves dev time; easier debugging                 |
| **Reporting & reconciliation**       | Good                     | Good, with cleaner UI               | Razorpay’s dashboard is more intuitive           |
